H.E EDWARD KIWANUKA SSEKANDI﻿


Ssekandi was born in Masaka district on January 19, 1943. He graduated with honors from the University of East Africa with the Degree of Bachelor of Laws(LLB). He also holds a Diploma in Legal practice from the Law Development Center in Kampala.

From 1973 until 1978, he served as a lecturer at the Uganda Law Development Center. Between 1978 and 1979, he served as the acting director of the Law Development Center. He was lead council on the Commission of inquiry into Violation of Human Rights, between 1986 and 1993.
